"{\n  \"text\": \"Today I'm going to take some of the soil that I've been working on in my worm patch and use it for my front shrubs, which I just replanted. I lost a minor freeze. And this is some of the uh soil got this is the deeper, darker stuff. There's a good aggregate full of earthworms. And this is the living stuff that I'm going to try to incorporate to try to revive this beat-up old dead soil that was in the shrubs. Most all of our soil, because we put chemical fertilizers on it and all this other stuff, is in pretty bad shape. And this place, this was no exception. As I cut out the old beds, I found just about no earthworms. So I'm trying to reinvigorate that life. I'm put a bunch of good aggregate uh soil that I've uh composted all this time and let the worm patch. And then I'm gonna cover it with uh kind of a layer of mulch leaves. Uh this is from the compost pile as well, but it's more of the newer stuff. It's some of the leafier stuff, a lot more carbonous. I'm gonna put it on top just to create a cover for that good aggregate, uh give a good home for those earthworms, and this is what it looks like when it's done. Uh hopefully I can reinvigorate this dead soil.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Today I'm going to take some of the soil that I've been working on in my worm patch and use it for my front shrubs, which I just replanted.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 6.16,\n      \"duration\": 5.84,\n      \"confidence\": 0.995,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Toda\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence